    [ctns_front]
Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
A Linear Function is a function that can be 
written in the form,
$|y=mx+b,|$
where $$m$$ and $$b$$ are constants, $$m \ne 0$$.
    [/ctns_back]
    
    [ctns_backspeak]
A Linear Function is a function that can be 
written in the form,
y equals em times x plus b,
where em and bee are constants, with em not equal to zero.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
    

[/ctns_make]
